{
  "texts": [
    "We expand on this argument, which we test in a rigorous way.",
    "We call this third approach the machine bias hypothesis, a concept we develop and clarify in the following section along with other important concepts.",
    "Bias can be understood as \"prejudice or favoritism toward an individual or group based on their inherent or acquired characteristics\" (Mehrabi et al., 2021).",
    "As such, it is certainly one of the most important objects of contemporary sociological investigation.",
    "Algorithmic bias, the bias produced by algorithms that make use of social data, has also been extensively analyzed."
  ]
}